Paper: hep-th/9407134

Date: 1994-07-21

Title: The Topological CP^1 Model and the Large-N Matrix Integral

Authors: T. Eguchi and S.-K. Yang

Comments: 13 pages, LaTeX, UT-684

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A9 (1994) 2893-2902

We discuss the topological $CP^1$ model which consists of the holomorphicmaps from Riemann surfaces onto $CP^1$. We construct a large-$N$ matrix modelwhich reproduces precisely the partition function of the $CP^1$ model at allgenera of Riemann surfaces. The action of our matrix model has the form ${\rmTr}\, V(M)=-2{\rm Tr}\, M(\log M -1) +2\sum t_{n,P}{\rm Tr}\, M^n(\log M-c_n)+\sum 1/n\cdot t_{n-1,Q}{\rm Tr}\, M^n~(c_n=\sum_1^n 1/j )$ where $M$ is an$N\times N$ hermitian matrix and $t_{n,P}\, (t_{n,Q}),~(n=0,1,2,\cdots)$ arethe coupling constants of the $n$-th descendant of the puncture (K\"ahler)operator.